detailed_description: An integrated Python library for negative design in high-throughput screening (HTS) and virtual screening (VS). It provides filters to remove undesirable compounds (e.g., PAINS, frequent hitters) from chemical libraries.

name: GEOM
one_line_profile: Energy-annotated molecular conformation dataset and API
detailed_description: A large-scale dataset of energy-annotated molecular conformations for machine learning in chemistry. The repository provides access to the data and utilities for processing these conformations.

name: scikit-chem
one_line_profile: High-level cheminformatics package built on RDKit
detailed_description: A cheminformatics library for the Scientific Python stack that provides a more pythonic and high-level interface to RDKit and Open Babel functionalities for molecular manipulation and analysis.

name: PIDGINv3
one_line_profile: Protein target prediction using random forests
detailed_description: A tool for predicting protein targets for small molecules using random forest models and reliability-density neighbourhood analysis, aiding in target identification and off-target prediction.

name: eMolFrag
one_line_profile: Molecular fragmentation tool based on BRICS
detailed_description: A Python-based tool for fragmenting molecules into building blocks using the BRICS algorithm. It is useful for fragment-based drug design and library generation.

name: dockey
one_line_profile: Integrated tool for molecular docking and virtual screening
detailed_description: An integrated software tool designed to streamline molecular docking and virtual screening workflows, likely providing a unified interface for preparing ligands/receptors and running docking simulations.

name: PoseBusters
one_line_profile: Plausibility checks for generated molecule poses using geometric and chemical constraints
detailed_description: A Python tool designed to perform sanity checks on generated molecule poses, ensuring they are chemically and physically plausible. It evaluates bond lengths, angles, clashes, and other stereochemical properties to filter out unrealistic docking or generative model outputs.

name: Molecular Rectifier
one_line_profile: Automated correction tool for unsanitizable RDKit molecules
detailed_description: A utility designed to fix common valence and connectivity errors in molecular structures that fail RDKit sanitization. It iteratively attempts to correct the molecule structure to make it chemically valid and processable.

name: RDKit to Params
one_line_profile: Tool to generate Rosetta params files from RDKit molecules for protein modeling
detailed_description: A Python module that facilitates the conversion of RDKit molecule objects into Rosetta parameter files (topology files). This enables the use of small molecules prepared in RDKit within the Rosetta software suite for docking and design tasks.

name: pkasolver
one_line_profile: Graph convolutional network toolkit for predicting pKa values of small molecules
detailed_description: A machine learning toolkit that uses Graph Convolutional Networks (GCNs) to predict the pKa values of small molecules. It provides a workflow for training models and predicting acid dissociation constants, crucial for understanding molecular behavior in biological systems.

name: MolVS
one_line_profile: Molecule validation and standardization library based on RDKit
detailed_description: A Python library built on top of RDKit for validating, standardizing, and salt stripping of chemical structures. It ensures consistency in chemical datasets by handling tautomers, normalization, and fragment removal.

name: OpenBabel Node
one_line_profile: Node.js bindings for the Open Babel chemical toolbox
detailed_description: Provides Node.js bindings for the Open Babel C++ library, enabling developers to perform chemical file conversion and data processing within JavaScript/Node.js environments.

name: Molecular Transformer Embeddings
one_line_profile: Transformer-based model to generate molecular embeddings from text representations
detailed_description: A deep learning tool that utilizes Transformer architectures to translate molecular text representations (like SMILES/InChI) into continuous vector embeddings, facilitating downstream machine learning tasks in drug discovery.

name: Diffusion Conformer
one_line_profile: Diffusion-based generative model for small molecule conformer generation
detailed_description: An implementation of a diffusion probabilistic model specifically designed for generating diverse and energetically favorable 3D conformers of small molecules from 2D graphs.

name: ODDT
one_line_profile: Open Drug Discovery Toolkit for virtual screening, interaction scoring, and machine learning
detailed_description: A modular and comprehensive toolkit for computer-aided drug discovery (CADD). It provides unified interfaces for various docking software, scoring functions (including RF-Score and NN-Score), and interaction fingerprint generation.

name: Open Babel
one_line_profile: Chemical toolbox for converting between chemical file formats and analyzing molecular data
detailed_description: A standard chemical toolbox designed to speak the many languages of chemical data. It allows searching, converting, analyzing, and storing data from molecular modeling, chemistry, solid-state materials, biochemistry, or related areas.

name: TorsionNet
one_line_profile: Deep neural network for predicting small molecule torsion energy profiles
detailed_description: A deep learning model developed to predict the torsion energy profiles of small molecules with accuracy comparable to Quantum Mechanics (QM) methods, facilitating faster conformational analysis.

name: PLIP
one_line_profile: Protein-Ligand Interaction Profiler for analyzing non-covalent interactions in PDB files
detailed_description: A tool for fully automated detection and visualization of relevant non-covalent protein-ligand interactions in 3D structures. It handles hydrogen bonds, hydrophobic contacts, pi-stacking, and more.

name: optking
one_line_profile: Molecular geometry optimization program typically used with quantum chemistry packages
detailed_description: A Python-based molecular geometry optimization library. It is designed to work with quantum chemistry software (like Psi4) to find equilibrium structures and transition states of molecules.

name: RDKit
one_line_profile: Collection of cheminformatics and machine learning software for molecular data processing
detailed_description: The industry-standard open-source cheminformatics software toolkit. It provides extensive functionality for molecule manipulation, descriptor calculation, fingerprint generation, substructure searching, and molecular visualization.

name: RDKit.js
one_line_profile: JavaScript port of the RDKit cheminformatics library
detailed_description: A comprehensive cheminformatics and molecule rendering toolkit for JavaScript environments, enabling client-side molecular manipulation, substructure search, and visualization within web applications.

name: RDKit_mETKDG
one_line_profile: Modified ETKDG workflow for conformer generation
detailed_description: A specialized implementation of the ETKDG (Experimental-Torsion Knowledge Distance Geometry) algorithm with modifications for improved conformer generation, provided as a Dockerized workflow.

name: chemicalite
one_line_profile: SQLite extension for cheminformatics
detailed_description: A chemical database extension for SQLite that adds support for molecular data types, substructure search, and chemical descriptors directly within the database engine.

name: ConfID
one_line_profile: Conformational characterization method for small molecules
detailed_description: An analytical tool for characterizing the conformational space of small molecules using molecular dynamics trajectories, aiding in the identification of relevant conformers.

name: P3DFFT++
one_line_profile: Parallel 3D Fast Fourier Transform library
detailed_description: A high-performance, scalable library for computing parallel 3D Fast Fourier Transforms, essential for simulating multiscale phenomena in molecular dynamics and materials science.

name: ETFlow
one_line_profile: Equivariant Flow Matching for molecular conformer generation
detailed_description: A deep learning model implementing equivariant flow matching to generate valid and diverse 3D molecular conformers.

name: pgchem
one_line_profile: PostgreSQL extension for chemical data
detailed_description: A PostgreSQL extension integrating OpenBabel functionality, allowing for storage, indexing, and querying of chemical structures and substructures directly within the database.

name: AVATREE
one_line_profile: Modelling framework for airway tree conformations
detailed_description: A computational tool for generating anatomically valid airway tree conformations from CT data and simulating broncho-constriction, useful for pulmonary studies.

name: UnifiedMolPretrain
one_line_profile: Unified 2D and 3D pre-training for molecular representations
detailed_description: A deep learning framework for pre-training molecular representations by integrating both 2D graph and 3D geometric information to improve downstream task performance.

name: pharmacophore-toolkit
one_line_profile: Toolkit for generating pharmacophore models from RDKit
detailed_description: A set of tools to generate, visualize, and manipulate simple pharmacophore models derived from molecular structures using RDKit.

name: moltiverse
one_line_profile: Enhanced sampling for molecular conformer generation
detailed_description: A tool for generating molecular conformers using enhanced sampling methods, designed to explore conformational space more effectively.

name: molplotly
one_line_profile: Interactive molecule visualization for Plotly
detailed_description: An extension to Plotly that enables interactive visualization of molecular structures on mouseover events within scatter plots, facilitating chemical data analysis.

name: MF-SuP-pKa
one_line_profile: Multi-fidelity pKa prediction model
detailed_description: A PyTorch implementation of a multi-fidelity modeling approach with subgraph pooling mechanism for accurate pKa prediction of small molecules.

name: RDMC
one_line_profile: Reaction Data and Molecular Conformers package
detailed_description: A Python package for handling chemical reactions, molecules, and their conformers, with a focus on 3D structural manipulation and analysis.

name: GMVAE
one_line_profile: Gaussian Mixture VAE for molecular simulations
detailed_description: A tool for learning interpretable embeddings from molecular simulation data using Gaussian Mixture Variational Autoencoders, aiding in the analysis of conformational dynamics.

name: CompassDock
one_line_profile: Deep learning-based protein-ligand docking implementation
detailed_description: The official implementation of CompassDock, a method for protein-ligand docking, developed by BIMSB bioinformatics group.

name: rDock
one_line_profile: Fast and versatile open-source molecular docking program
detailed_description: An open-source docking program designed for High Throughput Virtual Screening (HTVS) and binding mode prediction, capable of docking small molecules against proteins and nucleic acids.

name: Vina-GPU
one_line_profile: OpenCL implementation of AutoDock Vina for GPU acceleration
detailed_description: A heterogeneous OpenCL implementation of AutoDock Vina designed to accelerate molecular docking simulations using GPU hardware.

name: Vina-GPU-2.0
one_line_profile: Accelerated AutoDock Vina and QuickVina on GPUs
detailed_description: The second version of Vina-GPU, accelerating AutoDock Vina and derived methods like QuickVina 2 and QuickVina-W using GPU parallelization.

name: Vina-GPU-2.1
one_line_profile: Improved GPU docking toolkit for virtual screening
detailed_description: An updated version of the Vina-GPU toolkit offering faster speeds and higher accuracy for large-scale virtual screening campaigns.

name: DockM8
one_line_profile: Consensus docking workflow for virtual screening
detailed_description: An all-in-one Structure-Based Virtual Screening (SBVS) workflow that implements consensus docking strategies to improve hit enrichment.

name: Vina-CUDA
one_line_profile: CUDA-accelerated AutoDock Vina
detailed_description: An implementation of AutoDock Vina optimized for NVIDIA GPUs using CUDA, providing significant speedups for docking simulations.

name: Confidence Bootstrapping
one_line_profile: Confidence bootstrapping procedure for protein-ligand docking
detailed_description: An implementation of the Confidence Bootstrapping protocol to enhance the reliability of protein-ligand docking predictions.

name: FlexAID
one_line_profile: Flexible Artificial Intelligence Docking software
detailed_description: FlexAID is a molecular docking program that uses a genetic algorithm for conformational search and allows for receptor flexibility. It is designed to predict the binding pose of small molecules to protein targets.

name: DSDP
one_line_profile: Deep Site and Docking Pose blind docking strategy
detailed_description: DSDP (Deep Site and Docking Pose) is a GPU-accelerated blind docking strategy that integrates deep learning-based binding site prediction with a modified AutoDock Vina-based pose sampling algorithm.

name: DSDPFlex
one_line_profile: Flexible-receptor docking with GPU acceleration
detailed_description: DSDPFlex is an extension of the DSDP docking tool that incorporates receptor flexibility into the docking process, utilizing GPU acceleration to handle the increased computational complexity.

name: qvina
one_line_profile: Accelerated version of AutoDock Vina
detailed_description: QVina (QuickVina) is a fork of AutoDock Vina that provides significant speedups for molecular docking calculations without sacrificing accuracy, optimized for high-throughput virtual screening.

name: FABind
one_line_profile: Fast and Accurate Protein-Ligand Binding prediction
detailed_description: FABind is a deep learning model for predicting protein-ligand binding structures. It optimizes the docking process by jointly modeling the protein-ligand interaction and conformation.

name: MolecularDocking
one_line_profile: Collection of notebooks and tools for molecular docking
detailed_description: A repository containing Jupyter notebooks and scripts to perform and analyze molecular docking simulations, serving as a lightweight workflow for educational and research purposes.

name: HASTEN
one_line_profile: Machine Learning Boosted Docking for virtual screening
detailed_description: HASTEN is a tool that accelerates structure-based virtual screening by using machine learning to predict docking scores, reducing the number of full docking calculations required.

name: RNAxplorer
one_line_profile: Tool to explore RNA conformation space
detailed_description: RNAxplorer is a tool from the ViennaRNA group designed to explore RNA conformational space through sampling techniques, aiding in the study of RNA structure and dynamics.

name: REstretto
one_line_profile: Fragment-based protein-ligand docking tool
detailed_description: REstretto (REuse of sub-STRuctures as an Effective Technique for protein-ligand docking TOol) is a virtual screening-oriented docking tool that utilizes fragment reuse techniques to improve docking efficiency and accuracy.

name: SAnDReS
one_line_profile: Statistical analysis environment for docking results and scoring functions
detailed_description: SAnDReS (Statistical Analysis of Docking Results and Scoring functions) is a computational environment for developing and analyzing machine-learning models to predict ligand-binding affinity. It provides tools for statistical analysis of docking outcomes.

name: watvina
one_line_profile: AutoDock Vina fork with explicit/implicit water models
detailed_description: watvina is a modified version of the AutoDock Vina engine that incorporates implicit or explicit water models to improve docking accuracy. It also supports pharmacophore and position-constrained docking.

name: Scalar Fields
one_line_profile: Equivariant scalar fields for molecular docking with FFT
detailed_description: This tool implements Equivariant Scalar Fields for molecular docking, utilizing Fast Fourier Transforms (FFT) to accelerate the docking process while maintaining equivariance properties.

name: Animal-in-Motion
one_line_profile: Pipeline for animal video data processing and pose prediction
detailed_description: Animal-in-Motion is a data collection and processing pipeline for animal videos. It includes annotations for masks, keypoints, depth, and occlusion, suitable for 3D/4D reconstruction, tracking, and pose prediction in biological research.

name: Protenix-Dock
one_line_profile: End-to-end trainable protein-ligand docking framework
detailed_description: Protenix-Dock is an accurate and trainable end-to-end framework for protein-ligand docking. It leverages deep learning to predict binding poses directly.

name: AutoDock Vina
one_line_profile: Standard open-source molecular docking engine
detailed_description: AutoDock Vina is one of the most widely used open-source programs for molecular docking. It significantly improves the average accuracy of the binding mode predictions compared to AutoDock 4.

name: LigGrep
one_line_profile: Tool for filtering docked poses based on receptor-ligand interactions
detailed_description: LigGrep is a command-line tool designed to analyze and filter molecular docking results. It identifies docked poses that participate in specific user-defined receptor-ligand interactions, aiding in the selection of promising candidates.

name: Webina
one_line_profile: JavaScript/WebAssembly library for running AutoDock Vina in the browser
detailed_description: Webina is a library that ports AutoDock Vina to WebAssembly, enabling molecular docking calculations to run directly in a web browser on the client side.

name: Ringtail
one_line_profile: Analysis and storage package for virtual screenings with AutoDock
detailed_description: Ringtail is a Python package developed by the Forli Lab for managing, storing, and analyzing large-scale virtual screening results generated by AutoDock-GPU and AutoDock Vina.

name: DisCo-DiffDock
one_line_profile: Enhanced diffusion model for molecular docking with discrete latents
detailed_description: DisCo-DiffDock is an extension of the DiffDock model that incorporates discrete latents to enhance the continuous diffusion process for molecular docking tasks.

name: GNINA
one_line_profile: Deep learning framework for molecular docking
detailed_description: GNINA is a molecular docking software that utilizes deep convolutional neural networks to score protein-ligand poses, providing an alternative to traditional empirical scoring functions.

name: Phinder
one_line_profile: Pharmacophore feature identification using GNINA
detailed_description: Phinder is a tool for the semi-automatic identification of pharmacophore features from unbound receptor structures using GNINA fragment docking.

name: IDPConformerGenerator
one_line_profile: Conformational sampling tool for Intrinsically Disordered Proteins
detailed_description: A tool developed by the Forman-Kay Lab to build conformational representations of Intrinsically Disordered Proteins (IDPs) and Regions (IDRs) through guided sampling of protein torsion space.

name: autoparty
one_line_profile: Machine learning-guided visual inspection tool for molecular docking
detailed_description: Autoparty is a tool from Keiser Lab that assists in the visual inspection of molecular docking results using machine learning guidance, helping to prioritize poses for manual review.

name: LightDock-Rust
one_line_profile: Rust implementation of the LightDock docking software
detailed_description: A Rust port of the LightDock macromolecular docking software, aiming for performance improvements and memory safety provided by the Rust language.

name: Str2Str
one_line_profile: Score-based framework for zero-shot protein conformation sampling
detailed_description: Str2Str is a score-based generative framework for sampling protein conformations in a zero-shot manner, enabling the exploration of protein structural diversity without extensive training on specific targets.

name: TankBind
one_line_profile: Deep learning model for protein-ligand binding structure prediction
detailed_description: TankBind is a deep learning model that predicts protein-ligand binding structures and affinities. It treats the binding pocket as a 'tank' to capture interactions.

name: Boltzina
one_line_profile: Docking-guided binding prediction tool for virtual screening
detailed_description: A virtual screening tool that combines docking with deep learning-based binding prediction (Boltz-2) to achieve efficient and accurate identification of active compounds.

name: ab_opt
one_line_profile: Generative diffusion models for antibody design and docking
detailed_description: Implementation of generative diffusion models specifically tailored for the design, docking, and optimization of antibodies.

name: screenlamp
one_line_profile: Toolkit for hypothesis-driven virtual screening
detailed_description: A Python toolkit designed to facilitate hypothesis-driven virtual screening workflows, allowing for customized filtering and selection of ligand candidates.

name: siteinterlock
one_line_profile: Graph-based pose selection for protein-ligand docking
detailed_description: A tool that applies graph theory to improve pose selection in protein-ligand docking, aiming to identify the most probable binding conformations.

name: FABFlex
one_line_profile: Fast and accurate blind flexible docking model
detailed_description: Official implementation of the ICLR 2025 paper 'Fast and Accurate Blind Flexible Docking', providing a deep learning model for flexible protein-ligand docking.

name: docking_py
one_line_profile: Python library for automating molecular docking with Vina/Smina
detailed_description: A Python library that simplifies the automation and scripting of molecular docking tasks using Smina, Vina, and their variants.

name: VSDS-VD
one_line_profile: Benchmarking framework for AI-powered docking methods in virtual screening
detailed_description: A repository for benchmarking AI-powered docking methods specifically from the perspective of virtual screening, providing datasets and evaluation scripts.

name: Auto_AutoDock-GPU
one_line_profile: Batch processing tools for high-throughput protein-ligand docking with AutoDock-GPU
detailed_description: A set of tools designed to facilitate high-throughput protein-ligand docking in batch mode utilizing the AutoDock-GPU engine.

name: AutoDock VinaXB
one_line_profile: AutoDock Vina variant with halogen bond scoring function (XBSF)
detailed_description: An implementation of XBSF, a new empirical halogen bond scoring function, integrated into AutoDock Vina to improve docking accuracy for halogenated ligands.

name: VS-autodock-vina
one_line_profile: AutoDock Vina extension for virtual screening analysis
detailed_description: A modified version of AutoDock Vina that adds functionality specifically for analyzing virtual screening results.

name: mvina
one_line_profile: Modified version of AutoDock Vina for Linux
detailed_description: A modified implementation of the AutoDock Vina docking engine, optimized for Linux environments.

name: VinaSH
one_line_profile: AutoDock Vina variant accounting for Sigma Hole interactions
detailed_description: An improved version of AutoDock Vina that incorporates Sigma Hole interactions into the scoring function for better docking accuracy.

name: FlexPose
one_line_profile: AI-based framework for flexible protein-ligand binding pose modeling
detailed_description: A framework for AI-based flexible modeling of protein-ligand binding poses, addressing the flexibility of both ligand and protein during docking.

name: FlexDock
one_line_profile: Flexible docking and relaxation using composed unbalanced flows
detailed_description: Implementation of a method for flexible docking and relaxation by composing unbalanced flows, as presented at ICLR 2025.

name: IGModel
one_line_profile: Simultaneous prediction of ligand docking pose RMSD and binding strength
detailed_description: A deep learning model capable of simultaneously predicting the RMSD of a ligand docking pose and its binding strength against the target protein.

name: PointDE
one_line_profile: Protein docking evaluation using 3D point cloud neural networks
detailed_description: Official implementation of PointDE, a deep learning model that evaluates protein docking poses by representing them as 3D point clouds to predict the quality of the docking.

name: GatorAffinity
one_line_profile: Protein-ligand binding affinity prediction using synthetic structural data
detailed_description: A deep learning model designed to boost protein-ligand binding affinity prediction by leveraging large-scale synthetic structural data for training.

name: protein_mutation_scoring
one_line_profile: Scoring functions for protein mutation effects using ESM-2
detailed_description: A collection of scoring functions leveraging the ESM-2 protein language model to predict the effects of mutations on protein sequences.

name: Generalized-Score-Functions-for-Causal-Discovery
one_line_profile: Generalized score-based method for causal discovery
detailed_description: A MATLAB implementation of generalized score functions for causal discovery, enabling the identification of causal structures from data.

name: NeoBert
one_line_profile: Neoantigen-HLA binding affinity prediction using BERT
detailed_description: A BERT-based deep learning model specifically designed to predict the binding affinity between neoantigens and HLA molecules, integrating biological features.

name: BINDKIN
one_line_profile: Benchmark for kinase-ligand interaction point mutations
detailed_description: A structural benchmark dataset and toolset for measuring the impact of point mutations on kinase-ligand interactions.

name: BACPI
one_line_profile: Bi-directional attention neural network for compound-protein interaction
detailed_description: A deep learning model using bi-directional attention mechanisms to predict compound-protein interactions and binding affinity.

name: ms2rescore
one_line_profile: AI-assisted rescoring of peptide identifications in proteomics
detailed_description: A modular platform for AI-assisted rescoring of peptide identifications from mass spectrometry data, improving identification rates.

name: spectrum_similarity
one_line_profile: Scoring functions for comparing MS/MS spectra
detailed_description: A library of scoring functions designed to calculate the similarity between mass spectrometry (MS/MS) spectra.

name: RNAdvisor
one_line_profile: Integrated wrapper for RNA 3D structure evaluation metrics
detailed_description: A docker-based wrapper that integrates multiple metrics and scoring functions for the evaluation of RNA 3D structures.

name: plif_validity
one_line_profile: Tool for assessing interaction recovery of predicted protein-ligand poses
detailed_description: Code and notebooks for assessing the interaction recovery of predicted protein-ligand poses, useful for validating docking results.

name: MD-IFP
one_line_profile: MD trajectory analysis using protein-ligand Interaction Fingerprints
detailed_description: A tool for analyzing Molecular Dynamics (MD) trajectories by calculating and monitoring protein-ligand Interaction Fingerprints (IFPs) over time.

name: pocketoptimizer
one_line_profile: Binding pocket optimization using force fields and scoring functions
detailed_description: A tool for optimizing binding pockets based on force fields and docking scoring functions to improve ligand binding prediction.

name: dock2interaction_profile
one_line_profile: Batch analysis of protein-ligand interactions from docking results
detailed_description: A script wrapper around PLIP to perform batch analysis of protein-ligand interactions derived from Smina/Vina docking results.

name: CaFE_Plugin
one_line_profile: VMD plugin for binding affinity prediction using free energy methods
detailed_description: A VMD plugin that facilitates binding affinity prediction using end-point free energy methods such as MM/PBSA or MM/GBSA.

name: MGDTA
one_line_profile: Multigranular representation learning for drug-target binding affinity prediction
detailed_description: A deep learning model that explores multigranular representations to predict drug-target binding affinity, aiding in virtual screening and drug discovery.

name: DeepDTAF
one_line_profile: Deep learning architecture for protein-ligand binding affinity prediction
detailed_description: A deep learning framework that utilizes local and global features of proteins and ligands to predict binding affinity, supporting structure-based drug design.

name: AutoSF
one_line_profile: Automated search for bilinear scoring functions in knowledge graph learning
detailed_description: An automated machine learning (AutoML) tool designed to search for effective bilinear scoring functions for knowledge graph embedding, optimizing performance on link prediction tasks.

name: ERAS
one_line_profile: Efficient relation-aware scoring function search for knowledge graphs
detailed_description: A framework for efficiently searching for relation-aware scoring functions in knowledge graph embeddings, improving upon standard AutoML methods for KGE.

name: SCORE (SLAM)

detailed_description: A robotics algorithm for relocalization in semantic line maps using saturated consensus, applicable in SLAM (Simultaneous Localization and Mapping) tasks.

name: GPCNDTA
one_line_profile: Drug-target binding affinity prediction using cross-attention networks
detailed_description: A model for predicting drug-target binding affinity that integrates graph features and pharmacophores via cross-attention networks.

name: Seeing Without Looking
one_line_profile: Contextual rescoring of object detections for AP maximization
detailed_description: A computer vision tool that uses contextual information to rescore object detections, aiming to maximize Average Precision (AP) in detection tasks.

name: CHOKO
one_line_profile: Consensus rescoring of protein-protein docking poses
detailed_description: A tool for the consensus rescoring of protein-protein docking poses, utilizing the DockingPP library to improve docking predictions.

name: Alfalfa
one_line_profile: Web service for runtime interaction with building energy models
detailed_description: A platform enabling runtime interaction and control of building energy models (OpenStudio/EnergyPlus/Modelica) via REST APIs, used for energy optimization research.

name: DualBind
one_line_profile: 3D structure-based deep learning for binding affinity prediction
detailed_description: A deep learning model using a dual-loss framework to predict protein-ligand binding affinity from 3D structural data.

name: MSBooster
one_line_profile: Deep learning feature augmentation for PSM rescoring
detailed_description: A tool that generates deep learning-based features to improve Peptide-Spectrum Match (PSM) rescoring in proteomics, designed to work with Percolator.

name: PaccMann Kinase Binding
one_line_profile: Kinase binding residues analysis for affinity prediction
detailed_description: A module from the PaccMann project focusing on comparing active site and full kinase sequences for drug-target affinity prediction.

name: TFAIP Hybrid CTC-S2S
one_line_profile: Rescoring sequence-to-sequence models for text recognition
detailed_description: A framework for rescoring Sequence-to-Sequence models using CTC-Prefixes to improve text line recognition accuracy.

name: bg_control
one_line_profile: Blood glucose outcome improvement and meal scoring
detailed_description: A tool for analyzing time-series blood glucose data, identifying unlabelled meals, and developing meal-scoring functions to improve diabetes management outcomes.

name: SCORCH
one_line_profile: Scoring function and docking pipeline
detailed_description: Deployable code for the SCORCH scoring function and associated docking pipeline, designed for evaluating protein-ligand interactions.

name: IoT Attack Detection
one_line_profile: ML-based attack and anomaly detection for IoT sensors
detailed_description: A machine learning framework for detecting attacks and anomalies in IoT sensor networks, comparing various algorithms like Random Forest and ANN.

name: SCORE (Bioinfo)
one_line_profile: Consensus tool for detecting differentially expressed genes in bacteria
detailed_description: A consensus-based tool for identifying differentially expressed genes in bacterial transcriptomics data.

name: multiscorer
one_line_profile: Multiple metric functions for scikit-learn cross-validation
detailed_description: A utility module that enables the use of multiple scoring metrics simultaneously within scikit-learn's cross_val_score function.

name: XLM-Tools
one_line_profile: Program for scoring protein structures based on crosslinking mass spectrometry data
detailed_description: A Python-based tool designed to score and validate protein structural models using experimental data from crosslinking mass spectrometry (XL-MS), specifically supporting MonoLinks (MoDS), Crosslinks (MNXL), and both (XLMO).

name: AA-Score-Tool
one_line_profile: Tool for protein-ligand binding affinity prediction
detailed_description: A computational tool designed to predict the binding affinity of protein-ligand complexes, likely utilizing amino acid specific scoring contributions.

name: aafragpy
one_line_profile: High-energy hadronic interaction model implementation
detailed_description: A Python implementation of the AAfrag model for simulating high-energy hadronic interactions, based on QGSJET-II-04m, used in particle physics and astrophysics simulations.

name: NRLMFb
one_line_profile: Beta-distribution-rescored matrix factorization for DTI prediction
detailed_description: A method improving drug-target interaction prediction using Neighborhood Regularized Logistic Matrix Factorization with Beta-distribution rescoring.

name: AUTOSURF
one_line_profile: Automated construction of global potential energy surfaces
detailed_description: A software package for robustly computing electronic energies and automating the construction of global potential energy surfaces (PES), particularly for systems with highly anisotropic interactions.

name: MAGI
one_line_profile: Metabolite-gene annotation consensus scoring tool
detailed_description: A tool to score and find consensus between metabolite identifications and gene annotations to improve metabolomics and genomics integration.

name: FLOWUnsteady
one_line_profile: Interactional aerodynamics and acoustics solver
detailed_description: A solver for interactional aerodynamics and acoustics, specifically designed for multirotor aircraft and wind energy applications, simulating unsteady flow physics.

name: DeepRescore
one_line_profile: Deep learning-based PSM rescoring tool
detailed_description: A tool for rescoring peptide-spectrum matches (PSMs) in proteomics by leveraging deep learning-derived peptide features to improve identification accuracy.

name: GEMS

name: ProLIF (cbouy)

detailed_description: A library to generate interaction fingerprints for protein-ligand complexes, facilitating the analysis of molecular interactions from docking or MD simulations.

name: DeltaVina
one_line_profile: A scoring function for protein-ligand docking based on AutoDock Vina
detailed_description: DeltaVina is a scoring function designed to improve the accuracy of protein-ligand docking. It is often used in conjunction with a modified version of AutoDock Vina (vina4dv) to evaluate binding poses and affinities.

name: transkit

detailed_description: A set of pharmacokinetic tools and Jupyter notebooks designed for simulating and analyzing transgender hormone therapy regimens.

name: nlmixr2autoinit

detailed_description: An R package for the automatic generation of initial estimates for population pharmacokinetic modelling, developed by UCL Pharmacometrics.

name: soapgp

detailed_description: A Python implementation for predicting molecular properties using Gaussian Processes (GP) combined with the Smooth Overlap of Atomic Positions (SOAP) kernel.

detailed_description: Implementation of Knowledge-based BERT (K-BERT) adapted for molecular property prediction tasks.

name: ChemicalX

detailed_description: A PyTorch-based library designed for drug pair scoring tasks, enabling the prediction of drug-drug interactions, polypharmacy side effects, and drug synergy using state-of-the-art deep learning models.

detailed_description: A deep learning framework implementing SE(3)-equivariant networks for processing 3D geometric graphs, particularly useful for protein structure analysis and modeling.

name: GCPNet-EMA

name: bio-diffusion

detailed_description: Implementation of a geometry-complete diffusion generative model (GCDM) designed for generating and optimizing 3D molecular structures.

name: GGME

detailed_description: A library providing practical solutions and metrics for evaluating graph generative models, addressing pitfalls in standard evaluation procedures for molecular graphs.

name: Polygraph Benchmark

detailed_description: A framework designed to benchmark various graph generative models, facilitating the comparison of different approaches in molecular and graph generation.

name: PES-Learn

detailed_description: A software package that automates the generation of machine learning models for molecular potential energy surfaces (PES) by sampling geometries and running quantum chemistry calculations.

name: ESM-S

detailed_description: A protein language model that incorporates structural information, useful for tasks such as inverse folding and protein sequence design.

name: TorchDrug

detailed_description: A comprehensive machine learning platform designed for drug discovery, covering tasks related to graphs, proteins, and molecules, providing a unified interface for various datasets and models.

name: Mol-AIR

detailed_description: A library for vectorizing molecules (SMILES) and generating batches for training deep learning models in cheminformatics.

name: PKU_MDAgent

detailed_description: An agent based on Large Language Models designed to generate code and automate molecular dynamics simulations for obtaining material thermodynamic parameters.

name: CDGS

detailed_description: A conditional diffusion model based on discrete graph structures designed for molecular graph generation, enabling the generation of molecules with specific desired properties.

detailed_description: Implementation of a variational autoencoder (VAE) for molecules, allowing for the conversion of discrete molecular structures into a continuous latent space for optimization and property prediction.

name: MADGEN

detailed_description: A generative model that utilizes mass spectrometry data to guide the de novo generation of molecular structures, aiding in structure elucidation and identification.

name: controlled-peptide-generation

detailed_description: A framework for accelerating antimicrobial peptide discovery using controllable deep generative models coupled with molecular dynamics simulations to screen and optimize candidates.

name: GOFA
one_line_profile: Generative One-For-All model for joint graph language modeling
detailed_description: A generative framework capable of handling various graph-related tasks, including molecular graph generation and modeling, through a unified language modeling approach.

name: PINNs-based-MPC
one_line_profile: Nonlinear model predictive control using Physics-Informed Neural Networks
detailed_description: A framework implementing nonlinear model predictive control (NMPC) for multi-body dynamics by approximating system dynamics using Physics-Informed Neural Networks (PINNs).

name: Argenomic
one_line_profile: Quality-diversity algorithm for small molecule optimization
detailed_description: An implementation of a quality-diversity (illumination) algorithm designed for the exploration and optimization of small organic molecules.

name: Bayesian-Illumination

detailed_description: A Bayesian Illumination approach for accelerating the generative optimization of small molecules, focusing on diverse and high-quality molecular discovery.

name: paper2lkg

detailed_description: A pipeline leveraging Large Language Models (LLMs) to extract structured information from academic papers and construct local Knowledge Graphs (KG), facilitating scientific literature mining.

name: LH2Transfer

detailed_description: A MATLAB-based simulation tool for quantifying transfer and boil-off losses in Liquid Hydrogen (LH2) supply chains, enabling optimization of storage and refueling infrastructure.

name: AI4Sci-MiCaM
one_line_profile: De novo molecular generation via connection-aware motif mining
detailed_description: A molecular generation framework that uses connection-aware motif mining to construct chemically valid and optimized molecules, as presented at ICLR 2023.

name: poli-baselines
one_line_profile: Objective functions and black-box optimization algorithms for bio-molecules
detailed_description: A collection of baselines, objective functions, and black-box optimization algorithms specifically tailored for protein and small molecule engineering tasks.

name: AliDiff
one_line_profile: Target-aware molecule diffusion with exact energy optimization
detailed_description: A diffusion-based model for generating molecules that align with specific targets using exact energy optimization techniques, presented at NeurIPS 2024.

name: rlmolecule
one_line_profile: Reinforcement learning library for material and molecule optimization
detailed_description: A library designed to apply reinforcement learning techniques specifically for the optimization of materials and molecular structures, facilitating the discovery of novel compounds with desired properties.

name: NeVAE
one_line_profile: Deep generative model for molecular graphs
detailed_description: Implementation of the NeVAE model (AAAI 2019), a variational autoencoder designed for generating molecular graphs, enabling the exploration of chemical space.

name: CSLVAE
one_line_profile: Graph generative model for navigating combinatorial synthesis libraries
detailed_description: Implements the Combinatorial Synthesis Library Variational Auto-Encoder (CSLVAE), an efficient graph generative model designed to navigate and generate molecules from ultra-large combinatorial synthesis libraries.

name: ResGen
one_line_profile: 3D molecular generation method
detailed_description: A computational method for 3D molecular generation, focusing on creating valid molecular structures in three-dimensional space.

name: Drug Repurposing with TigerGraph
one_line_profile: Drug repurposing using graph machine learning
detailed_description: A project utilizing TigerGraph and Graph Machine Learning techniques to identify potential drug repurposing opportunities.

name: paccmann_generator
one_line_profile: Transcriptomic or protein-driven molecular design generator
detailed_description: Generative models for molecular design that are driven by transcriptomic data or protein targets, part of the PaccMann ecosystem.

name: paccmann_kinase_binding_residues
one_line_profile: Kinase binding residue analysis for affinity prediction and generation
detailed_description: Code for comparing active site and full kinase sequences to improve drug-target affinity prediction and molecular generation tasks.

name: SimGen
one_line_profile: Zero-shot molecular generation via similarity kernels
detailed_description: Implements a zero-shot molecular generation approach utilizing similarity kernels to generate novel molecules without extensive training on specific datasets.

name: Drug-Combo-Generator
one_line_profile: Deep generative models for drug combination generation
detailed_description: A deep generative model framework for generating drug combinations (graph sets) by leveraging hierarchical disease network embeddings.

name: CREBM
one_line_profile: Preference optimization for molecule synthesis with energy-based models
detailed_description: Implementation of Conditional Residual Energy-based Models (CREBM) for preference optimization in molecule synthesis, as presented at ICML 2024.

name: EMolCombiner
one_line_profile: Fragment-based molecule generation tool
detailed_description: A tool for de novo drug discovery that generates molecules by combining chemical fragments.

name: FASMIFRA
one_line_profile: Molecular generation by fast assembly of SMILES fragments
detailed_description: A tool for generating molecules through the fast assembly of SMILES fragments, facilitating efficient exploration of chemical space.

name: 3DLinker
one_line_profile: E(3) Equivariant Variational Autoencoder for molecular linker design
detailed_description: An E(3) equivariant variational autoencoder designed specifically for the task of molecular linker design, generating 3D structures that link molecular fragments.

name: GEMCODE
one_line_profile: Hybrid generative AI for de novo design of co-crystals
detailed_description: An automated screening pipeline leveraging a hybrid of generative AI and evolutionary optimization for the de novo design of pharmaceutical co-crystals with enhanced tabletability.

name: Cicero Word Generator
one_line_profile: Control software for atomic physics experiments
detailed_description: A user interface and control software suite designed for atomic physics experiments, capable of designing and running sequences on National Instruments digital and analog output cards.

name: MolDQN-pytorch
one_line_profile: Optimization of molecules via deep reinforcement learning
detailed_description: A PyTorch implementation of the MolDQN algorithm for optimizing molecular properties using deep reinforcement learning.

name: moo-denovo
one_line_profile: Multi-objective optimization for de novo molecular design
detailed_description: A tool for the automated de novo design of drug-like molecular libraries using deep learning-based multi-objective optimization techniques.

name: ORGANIC
one_line_profile: Objective-Reinforced Generative Adversarial Networks for Inverse-design Chemistry
detailed_description: ORGANIC is a framework for optimizing distributions of molecules using Objective-Reinforced Generative Adversarial Networks (ORGAN). It is designed for inverse design in chemistry, allowing for the generation of molecular structures with specific desired properties.

name: STONED-SELFIES
one_line_profile: Efficient molecular exploration and optimization algorithm using SELFIES
detailed_description: This repository implements the STONED (Superfast Traversal, Optimization, Novelty, Exploration and Discovery) algorithm. It utilizes the SELFIES molecular representation to perform efficient traversal and optimization in the chemical space, serving as a fast baseline for molecular generative models.

name: genmol
one_line_profile: Library for molecular structure generation
detailed_description: Genmol is a Python library designed for molecular structure generation. It provides functionalities to generate chemical structures, likely utilizing generative models to assist in drug discovery and chemical space exploration.

name: MolEvol
one_line_profile: Molecule optimization via explainable evolution
detailed_description: MolEvol implements a method for molecule optimization using explainable evolutionary algorithms. It aims to optimize molecular properties while providing interpretability in the generative process, useful for rational drug design.

name: DrugAssist
one_line_profile: Large Language Model for molecule optimization
detailed_description: DrugAssist is a Large Language Model (LLM) designed for molecule optimization. It treats molecular optimization as a translation task, enabling the generation of optimized molecules based on textual or structural prompts, facilitating human-in-the-loop drug design.

name: DEG
one_line_profile: Data-efficient graph grammar learning for molecular generation
detailed_description: A deep learning framework implementing graph grammar learning for efficient molecular generation, particularly effective in low-data regimes. It automates the extraction of production rules from molecular datasets to guide the generation process.

name: GraphDG
one_line_profile: Generative model for molecular distance geometry
detailed_description: A generative model designed to produce molecular conformations by predicting distance geometries. It leverages graph neural networks to model the spatial relationships between atoms in a molecule.

name: Scaffold Hopping WHALES
one_line_profile: Scaffold hopping and virtual screening using WHALES descriptors
detailed_description: A computational tool for drug discovery that performs scaffold hopping and virtual screening. It utilizes WHALES (Weighted Holistic Atom-Localization and Entity Shape) descriptors to identify chemically diverse molecular scaffolds with similar biological activities.

name: Guacamole
one_line_profile: Spark-based somatic variant calling and local assembly
detailed_description: A somatic variant caller built on Apache Spark, designed for high-throughput sequencing data. It supports multi-sample calling (including RNA-seq) and local assembly to identify genetic variants.

name: GDSS
one_line_profile: Score-based generative modeling of graphs via stochastic differential equations
detailed_description: A score-based generative framework for graphs that utilizes a system of stochastic differential equations (SDEs). It is designed to generate molecular graphs by modeling the diffusion process in the graph space.

name: DiffLinker
one_line_profile: Equivariant 3D-conditional diffusion model for molecular linker design
detailed_description: A 3D-conditional diffusion model specifically designed for molecular linker design. It generates molecular fragments that connect two or more disconnected substructures while maintaining E(3) equivariance.

name: ZOLA-3D
one_line_profile: Zernike Optimized Localization Algorithm for 3D single molecule localizations
detailed_description: A software tool for 3D single-molecule localization microscopy. It uses Zernike polynomials to model the point spread function (PSF) and optimize localization precision, enabling high-resolution 3D imaging.

name: BiAAE
one_line_profile: Molecular generation for desired transcriptome changes
detailed_description: A generative model using Adversarial Autoencoders (AAE) to design molecules that induce specific transcriptomic changes. It bridges chemical structure generation with biological gene expression profiles.

name: GGM
one_line_profile: Graph generative model for molecule generation
detailed_description: A graph-based generative model designed for the de novo generation of small molecular graphs. It focuses on learning the distribution of molecular structures to generate chemically valid compounds.

name: GB-GM
one_line_profile: Graph-based generative model for molecules
detailed_description: A graph-based generative model developed by the Jensen Group for molecular generation. It constructs molecules atom-by-atom or fragment-by-fragment using graph representations.

name: Graph Protein Design
one_line_profile: Generative models for graph-based protein design
detailed_description: A generative framework for protein design that represents proteins as graphs. It learns to generate amino acid sequences that fold into desired 3D structures, leveraging graph neural networks for structure-sequence modeling.

name: DiffHopp
one_line_profile: Graph diffusion model for scaffold hopping
detailed_description: A graph diffusion model specifically tailored for scaffold hopping in drug design. It generates novel molecular scaffolds while preserving key structural features and interactions of the original molecule.

name: gruenifai
one_line_profile: Interactive multi-parameter optimization of molecules
detailed_description: A tool for interactive multi-parameter optimization of molecules in a continuous vector space. It allows users to navigate the chemical space and optimize molecules based on multiple properties simultaneously.

name: Molecule Generator
one_line_profile: Multi-objective de novo drug design with conditional graph generation
detailed_description: A conditional graph generative model for multi-objective de novo drug design. It generates molecular graphs conditioned on desired properties, enabling the targeted design of drug-like molecules.

name: MolGAN-PyTorch
one_line_profile: PyTorch implementation of MolGAN for molecular generation
detailed_description: A PyTorch implementation of MolGAN, an implicit generative model for small molecular graphs. It uses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) to generate molecular structures directly.

name: RGFN
one_line_profile: Synthesizable molecular generation model using GFlowNets
detailed_description: Implementation of the RGFN (Robust GFlowNet) model for generating synthesizable molecules, as presented in NeurIPS 2024. It focuses on ensuring the chemical validity and synthesizability of generated molecular structures.

name: Graph-DiT
one_line_profile: Graph Diffusion Transformer for multi-conditional molecular generation
detailed_description: A deep learning model utilizing Graph Diffusion Transformers to generate molecular structures conditioned on multiple properties, aiming to improve the controllability of de novo drug design.

name: MoLeR
one_line_profile: Scaffold-constrained molecular generation model
detailed_description: Implementation of MoLeR, a graph-based generative model for molecules. It supports scaffold-constrained generation, allowing users to generate molecules that contain a specific core structure, which is critical for lead optimization in drug discovery.

name: RuSH
one_line_profile: Scaffold Hopping with Generative Reinforcement Learning for drug design
detailed_description: Official implementation of RuSH (Scaffold Hopping with Generative Reinforcement Learning). Includes ScaffoldFinder algorithm for 2D decoration identification, 3D shape-based scoring with ROCS, and scoring plugins for REINVENT. Enables structure-guided molecular generation for drug design.

name: S4-Drug-Design
one_line_profile: Chemical language modeling with structured state space sequence models
detailed_description: The official codebase of the paper 'Chemical language modeling with structured state space sequence models'. It applies Structured State Space Sequence (S4) models to de novo drug design and molecular generation tasks.

name: ChemTSv2
one_line_profile: Refined Python implementation of ChemTS for de novo molecule generation
detailed_description: A refined and extended version of ChemTS, a tool for de novo molecule generation using Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) and Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN). It facilitates the exploration of chemical space for drug discovery.

name: MolGAN
one_line_profile: Implicit generative model for small molecular graphs
detailed_description: Tensorflow implementation of MolGAN, an implicit generative model for small molecular graphs. It uses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and Reinforcement Learning to generate molecular graphs with desired properties.

name: Modof
one_line_profile: Implementation of Modof for Molecule Optimization
detailed_description: The implementation of Modof, a framework for molecule optimization. It is designed to modify molecular structures to optimize specific properties for drug discovery tasks.

name: OpenFF Recharge

detailed_description: An automated framework for generating optimized partial charges for molecules, developed by the Open Force Field Initiative. It supports the parameterization of force fields for molecular dynamics simulations.

name: TransVAE
one_line_profile: Transformer Based VAE Architecture for De Novo Molecular Design
detailed_description: A Transformer-based Variational Autoencoder (VAE) architecture designed for de novo molecular design. It leverages attention mechanisms to generate novel molecular structures.

name: GAML
one_line_profile: Genetic Algorithm Machine Learning for automated force field parameterization
detailed_description: Genetic Algorithm Machine Learning (GAML) software package for automated force field parameterization. It aids in optimizing parameters for computational chemistry simulations.

name: lammps_interface

detailed_description: A tool for the automatic generation of LAMMPS input files for molecular dynamics simulations of Metal-Organic Frameworks (MOFs). It simplifies the setup process for complex material simulations.

name: ConsensusCruncher

detailed_description: ConsensusCruncher is a tool that suppresses errors in next-generation sequencing (NGS) data by using unique molecular identifiers (UMIs) to amalgamate reads derived from the same DNA template into a consensus sequence.

name: QuantumMolGAN-PyTorch
one_line_profile: Quantum Generative Adversarial Networks for Generative Chemistry
detailed_description: Source code for 'Exploring the Advantages of Quantum Generative Adversarial Networks in Generative Chemistry'. It implements a Quantum GAN for molecular generation tasks.

name: Semla-Flow
one_line_profile: Efficient 3D molecular generation with flow-matching and Semla
detailed_description: Implements efficient 3D molecular generation using flow-matching techniques integrated with Semla. It is designed for generating 3D molecular conformers or structures.

name: GraphVAE-Approx
one_line_profile: Non-autoregressive graph variational autoencoder for molecular graph generation
detailed_description: An efficient learning framework for non-autoregressive Graph Variational Autoencoders (GraphVAE) designed for molecular graph generation, addressing computational bottlenecks in graph generation tasks.

name: LS-MolGen

detailed_description: A deep reinforcement learning method for target-specific molecular generation that utilizes both ligand and structure information to guide the generation process.

name: Matbench Genmetrics

detailed_description: A Python library providing standardized metrics for evaluating generative models in materials science, inspired by Guacamol and CDVAE benchmarks.

name: GDiffRetro

detailed_description: A deep learning model for retrosynthesis prediction that combines dual graph enhanced molecular representations with diffusion-based generation techniques.

name: Molecular VAE

detailed_description: Implementation of the Variational Autoencoder (VAE) for molecular design, enabling the conversion of discrete molecular representations into a continuous latent space for optimization.

name: GATNN-VS

detailed_description: A tool utilizing Graph Attention Networks (GAT) for improved scaffold hopping in ligand-based virtual screening, enhancing the discovery of novel chemotypes.

name: ChemTS

detailed_description: A Python library for de novo molecule design that combines Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) with a Recurrent Neural Network (RNN) to generate molecules with optimized properties.

name: Moltiverse
one_line_profile: Molecular conformer generation using enhanced sampling methods
detailed_description: A library for generating molecular conformers using enhanced sampling techniques, implemented in Crystal, aimed at exploring conformational space efficiently.

name: REINVENT-GDB13

detailed_description: Part of the REINVENT ecosystem, this tool uses a Recurrent Neural Network to generate molecules, specifically trained on the GDB-13 database of small organic molecules.

name: REINVENT-Randomized

detailed_description: An extension of the REINVENT framework that utilizes randomized SMILES strings during training to improve the diversity and quality of generated molecules.

name: REINVENT-Scaffold-Decorator

detailed_description: A tool within the REINVENT family for scaffold decoration, using an encoder-decoder architecture to generate molecules by elaborating on a given core scaffold.

name: GGM-metrics
one_line_profile: Evaluation metrics for graph generative models
detailed_description: A library providing a suite of evaluation metrics for graph generative models, essential for benchmarking performance in molecular generation and other graph-based tasks.

name: GenerativeLEGO

detailed_description: A deep learning framework for generating graph structures (specifically molecular graphs) by assembling sub-graph components, analogous to LEGO blocks. It focuses on fragment-based molecular generation.

name: hgraph2graph

name: JT-VAE

detailed_description: The official implementation of the Junction Tree Variational Autoencoder (JT-VAE), a seminal model that generates molecular graphs by first generating a junction tree of chemical substructures and then assembling them into a full molecule, guaranteeing 100% validity.

name: CoarseGrainingVAE

detailed_description: A Variational Autoencoder (VAE) based framework for performing geometric super-resolution on molecules. It learns to map coarse-grained molecular representations back to fine-grained all-atom geometries.

name: MolGAN-pytorch
one_line_profile: PyTorch implementation of MolGAN for small molecular graph generation
detailed_description: A PyTorch implementation of MolGAN, an implicit generative model for small molecular graphs that uses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and reinforcement learning objectives to generate molecules with desired properties.

name: MolReasoner

detailed_description: MolReasoner is a framework that combines molecular large language models with knowledge graphs to enable effective and interpretable reasoning for molecular tasks. It addresses the limitations of LLMs in domain-specific reasoning by integrating structured knowledge.

name: im4MEC

name: GraphSVX

name: SigDigger

name: EchoGNN

detailed_description: EchoGNN is a graph neural network-based model designed for estimating ejection fraction from echocardiograms. It incorporates explainability mechanisms to highlight relevant cardiac structures.

name: D4Explainer

detailed_description: D4Explainer is a generative graph explainer that uses discrete denoising diffusion probabilistic models to generate counterfactual explanations for Graph Neural Networks. It aims to provide in-distribution graph explanations.

name: GraphFramEx
one_line_profile: Systematic evaluation framework for GNN explainability methods
detailed_description: GraphFramEx is a comprehensive framework designed to evaluate and benchmark various explainability methods for Graph Neural Networks. It provides standard metrics and datasets to assess the quality of GNN explanations.

name: STExplainer
