detailed_description: STExplainer is a framework for providing explanations for spatio-temporal graph neural networks. It identifies salient spatial and temporal patterns that contribute to model predictions, applicable in domains like traffic flow or environmental monitoring.

name: UQ4DD
one_line_profile: Uncertainty Quantification library specifically designed for Drug Discovery pipelines
detailed_description: A Python library developed by MolecularAI (AstraZeneca) to provide uncertainty quantification methods for drug discovery models, enabling reliability assessment in molecular property prediction.

name: LIT (Learning Interpretability Tool)
one_line_profile: Interactive platform for visualizing and understanding ML model behavior
detailed_description: An open-source platform for visualization and understanding of machine learning models. It supports debugging, error analysis, and interpretability for various data types including text and tabular data used in scientific modeling.

name: GNNExplainer
one_line_profile: Model-agnostic explanation method for Graph Neural Networks
detailed_description: The reference implementation of GNNExplainer, a tool that provides interpretable explanations for predictions made by any Graph Neural Network, widely used in molecular graph analysis.

name: GNNExplainer_DGL
one_line_profile: DGL implementation of GNNExplainer for graph model interpretability
detailed_description: An implementation of the GNNExplainer algorithm using the Deep Graph Library (DGL), facilitating interpretability for DGL-based molecular models.

name: ReFine
one_line_profile: Multi-grained explainability method for Graph Neural Networks
detailed_description: Implementation of ReFine, a method for generating multi-grained explanations for GNN predictions, applicable to understanding molecular graph embeddings.

name: chemprop (Evidential)
one_line_profile: Chemprop fork with fast and scalable uncertainty quantification
detailed_description: A specialized version of Chemprop that implements Evidential Deep Learning for scalable uncertainty quantification in molecular property prediction and virtual screening.

name: StableGNN
one_line_profile: Framework for autonomous learning of explainable graph neural networks
detailed_description: A framework designed to learn stable and explainable Graph Neural Networks, addressing causality and interpretability in graph-based learning tasks.

name: WebPlotDigitizer
one_line_profile: Web-based tool to extract numerical data from plot images
detailed_description: A widely used tool in scientific research for extracting underlying numerical data from images of plots and charts found in papers, enabling data recovery and re-analysis.

name: Graph Network Explainability
one_line_profile: Explainability techniques for Graph Networks in chemistry
detailed_description: Implementation of explainability techniques (like Gradient-based methods) for Graph Convolutional Networks, specifically demonstrated on organic chemistry tasks and molecular graphs.

name: Transformers Interpret
one_line_profile: Model explainability tool for Hugging Face Transformers
detailed_description: A library to explain the output of Transformer models. While generic, it is applicable to scientific transformer models (e.g., in protein language models or SMILES transformers) for interpretability analysis.

name: Puncc
one_line_profile: Python library for predictive uncertainty quantification using conformal prediction
detailed_description: Puncc (Predictive UNcertainty Calibration and Conformalization) is a library designed to assess the reliability of machine learning models by providing uncertainty quantification metrics and conformal prediction methods.

name: DIG
one_line_profile: Dive into Graphs: A library for graph deep learning research and interpretability
detailed_description: DIG is a library for graph deep learning that includes unified implementations of data interfaces, common algorithms, and evaluation metrics, with a strong focus on graph generation and interpretability (XAI) for molecular graphs.

name: PGExplainer
one_line_profile: Parameterized Explainer for Graph Neural Networks
detailed_description: An implementation of PGExplainer, a method for explaining the predictions of Graph Neural Networks, often used for interpreting molecular property predictions.

name: Uncertainty Baselines
one_line_profile: High-quality implementations of standard and SOTA uncertainty quantification methods
detailed_description: A library providing implementations of various uncertainty quantification methods across different tasks, serving as a benchmark and toolkit for research in reliable machine learning.

name: crepes
one_line_profile: Python package for conformal prediction and calibration
detailed_description: Crepes (Conformal Regressors and Predictive Systems) is a Python package that implements conformal prediction methods to produce valid prediction intervals and assess model calibration.

name: Inseq
one_line_profile: Interpretability toolkit for sequence generation models
detailed_description: Inseq is a library for interpreting sequence generation models, allowing users to visualize and analyze feature attributions, applicable to biological sequence models (e.g., proteins, SMILES).

name: CrysXPP
one_line_profile: Explainable property predictor for crystalline materials
detailed_description: A deep learning model designed for predicting properties of crystalline materials with a focus on explainability, allowing researchers to understand feature importance in material structures.

name: ChemArr
one_line_profile: Physics-informed Chemprop model with Arrhenius equation
detailed_description: An extension of the Chemprop model that incorporates the Arrhenius equation into the output layer to add physical constraints and interpretability to molecular property predictions.

name: Gauche (Chemistry)
one_line_profile: Gaussian Process library for chemistry
detailed_description: A library designed to facilitate the use of Gaussian Processes in chemistry, providing tools for uncertainty quantification and molecular property prediction.

name: DL4SWAT
one_line_profile: Deep learning for SWAT model calibration
detailed_description: A scalable deep learning framework specifically designed for the calibration of the Soil and Water Assessment Tool (SWAT), aiding in hydrological modeling.

name: EEGCN
one_line_profile: Brain connectivity investigation with GNNs
detailed_description: A Graph Neural Network framework for analyzing EEG data to investigate brain connectivity, incorporating GNNExplainer for interpretability.

name: GCFExplainer
one_line_profile: Global Counterfactual Explainer for GNNs
detailed_description: An algorithm for generating global counterfactual explanations for Graph Neural Networks, helping to understand model decision boundaries in graph-based tasks.

name: Captum
one_line_profile: Model interpretability library for PyTorch
detailed_description: A comprehensive library for model interpretability and understanding in PyTorch, offering various algorithms to attribute model predictions to input features.

name: GraphXAI
one_line_profile: Benchmarking suite for GNN explainers
detailed_description: A library and dataset collection designed to support the development and evaluation of explainability methods for Graph Neural Networks.

name: GCNN-Explainability
one_line_profile: Explainability methods for Graph CNNs
detailed_description: Implementation of explainability methods for Graph Convolutional Neural Networks, providing tools to visualize and understand graph model predictions.

name: GNN-SubNet
one_line_profile: Disease subnetwork detection with explainable GNNs
detailed_description: A tool for detecting disease-relevant subnetworks within biological networks using explainable Graph Neural Networks.

name: explain_graphs
one_line_profile: Explainability methods for GCNNs (CVPR 2019)
detailed_description: Code implementation for explainability methods applied to Graph Convolutional Neural Networks, enabling analysis of graph classification models.

name: WaveBlocks
one_line_profile: Optimization framework for optics and deep learning
detailed_description: A framework for the joint optimization and calibration of optical systems and deep learning models, facilitating computational optics research.

name: MAPIE
one_line_profile: A scikit-learn-compatible library for uncertainty quantification using conformal prediction
detailed_description: MAPIE (Model Agnostic Prediction Interval Estimator) allows for estimating prediction intervals and controlling risks for regression and classification tasks. It implements conformal prediction methods to provide rigorous uncertainty quantification for machine learning models.

name: ADMET-AI
one_line_profile: ADMET property prediction platform using Chemprop
detailed_description: ADMET-AI provides a trained Chemprop-based model for predicting Absorption, Distribution, Metabolism, Excretion, and Toxicity (ADMET) properties of molecules. It offers both a Python API and a web interface for fast and accurate profiling of drug candidates.

name: tridesclous
one_line_profile: Offline and online spike sorting tool for electrophysiology
detailed_description: Tridesclous is a toolkit for spike sorting, designed to process extracellular recordings from multi-electrode arrays. It provides a complete pipeline including signal preprocessing, peak detection, feature extraction, clustering, and template matching for neuroscience research.

name: exmol
one_line_profile: Counterfactual explanations for molecular property prediction models
detailed_description: Exmol is a library for explaining black-box molecular property prediction models. It generates counterfactual examples (similar molecules with different properties) to provide interpretability for chemical machine learning models.

name: SLM4Mol
one_line_profile: Quantitative benchmark and analysis suite for molecular large language models
detailed_description: A comprehensive benchmark suite designed to evaluate Molecular Large Language Models (MolLLMs) across various downstream tasks in drug discovery and chemistry, facilitating quantitative analysis of model capabilities.

name: BigSMILES_homopolymer
one_line_profile: Automated BigSMILES conversion workflow for homopolymers
detailed_description: A workflow tool for converting homopolymeric macromolecules into the BigSMILES representation, facilitating the handling and analysis of polymer data.

name: ogb_lite
one_line_profile: Lightweight version of the Open Graph Benchmark (OGB)
detailed_description: A lightweight implementation of the Open Graph Benchmark (OGB) library that removes the dependency on PyTorch, facilitating graph learning benchmarks in diverse environments.

name: MolCap-Arena
one_line_profile: Benchmark for language-enhanced molecular property prediction and captioning
detailed_description: A comprehensive benchmark suite for evaluating models on molecular captioning and language-enhanced molecular property prediction tasks.

name: astartes
one_line_profile: Tool for rigorous data splitting in machine learning
detailed_description: A Python library for creating rigorous and reproducible data splits for machine learning, with specific support for chemical and scientific datasets (e.g., scaffold splitting).

name: SL_benchmark
one_line_profile: Benchmark for synthetic lethality prediction methods
detailed_description: A benchmarking study and codebase for evaluating various machine learning methods in the prediction of synthetic lethality, a key concept in cancer drug target discovery.

name: MolPuzzle
one_line_profile: Multimodal benchmark for molecular structure elucidation with LLMs
detailed_description: A benchmark dataset and framework designed to test the capabilities of Large Language Models (LLMs) in solving molecular puzzles, specifically focusing on molecular structure elucidation from multimodal data.

name: MolData
one_line_profile: Benchmark for disease and target-based molecular machine learning
detailed_description: A benchmark suite for evaluating machine learning models on molecular datasets specifically curated for disease and target-based drug discovery tasks.

name: Levenshtein SMILES Augmentation
one_line_profile: Data augmentation library for chemical reaction datasets using Levenshtein distance
detailed_description: A Python library designed to perform data augmentation on SMILES strings for chemical reactions. It utilizes Levenshtein distance to generate variations, helping to improve the robustness and generalization of machine learning models trained on reaction data.

name: paccmann_datasets
one_line_profile: Data loading utilities for PaccMann drug sensitivity prediction models
detailed_description: A library providing PyTorch dataset classes and data handling utilities for the PaccMann ecosystem, facilitating the training of models for anticancer drug sensitivity prediction using multi-modal data.

name: nonbonded
one_line_profile: Framework for optimizing and benchmarking molecular force fields
detailed_description: A management system and toolkit designed for the optimization and benchmarking of molecular force fields against physical property data. It automates the parameterization process for molecular dynamics simulations.

name: MUBen
one_line_profile: Benchmark for uncertainty quantification in molecular representation
detailed_description: A comprehensive benchmark suite designed to evaluate the performance of Uncertainty Quantification (UQ) methods applied to molecular representation models. It aims to standardize the assessment of model reliability in cheminformatics.

name: Tartarus
one_line_profile: Benchmarking platform for realistic inverse molecular design
detailed_description: Tartarus is a comparative benchmarking platform designed for inverse molecular design tasks. It focuses on realistic and practical scenarios, evaluating generative models not just on chemical validity but on their ability to optimize for complex, multi-objective properties relevant to drug discovery.

name: ChemGAN-challenge
one_line_profile: Benchmark code for ChemGAN drug discovery challenge
detailed_description: This repository contains the code and datasets for the ChemGAN challenge, which evaluates the ability of AI models (specifically GANs) to reproduce natural chemical diversity in drug discovery contexts. It serves as a reproduction suite and benchmark for generative chemistry.

name: Chemprop Benchmark
one_line_profile: Benchmarking scripts and data for Chemprop
detailed_description: This repository contains the benchmarking scripts and datasets used to evaluate the performance of the Chemprop model (v1). It provides a standardized environment for reproducing reported results and comparing molecular property prediction models.

name: Admetica
one_line_profile: ADMET property evaluation tool for Datagrok
detailed_description: Admetica is a repository (likely a plugin or package) for the Datagrok platform, focused on the evaluation of ADMET (Absorption, Distribution, Metabolism, Excretion, and Toxicity) properties of molecules. It facilitates the assessment of drug candidates.

name: DeepGene
one_line_profile: Deep learning tools for genomic datasets in drug discovery
detailed_description: DeepGene is a toolkit under the DeepChem ecosystem designed for working with genomic datasets. It aims to apply deep learning techniques to genomics for drug discovery purposes, providing specialized data handling and modeling capabilities.

name: DockString
one_line_profile: Dataset and benchmark for molecular docking
detailed_description: DockString is a Python package and dataset that facilitates realistic benchmarks for drug discovery. It provides a highly curated dataset of molecular docking scores and poses, along with tools to perform docking and evaluate machine learning models on these tasks.

name: HydroNet
one_line_profile: Benchmark tasks for preserving long-range interactions in molecular models
detailed_description: A benchmark suite consisting of tasks designed to test the ability of machine learning models to preserve long-range interactions and structural motifs in molecular data, specifically focusing on water clusters.

name: SEAL_OGB
one_line_profile: SEAL implementation for Open Graph Benchmark link prediction
detailed_description: An open-source implementation of the SEAL (Subgraphs, Embeddings, and Attributes for Link prediction) framework, specifically optimized for and evaluated on the Open Graph Benchmark (OGB) datasets.

name: OGB-LSC PCQM4Mv2 (Graphcore)
one_line_profile: Graphcore's solution for OGB Large Scale Challenge PCQM4Mv2
detailed_description: Implementation of Graph Neural Networks optimized for IPUs, designed for the OGB Large Scale Challenge (OGB-LSC) on the PCQM4Mv2 quantum chemistry dataset.

name: Guacamole (Hammerlab)
one_line_profile: Spark-based somatic variant calling tool
detailed_description: A somatic variant caller for next-generation sequencing data, built on Apache Spark to enable distributed processing of large genomic datasets.

name: Molecule Chef
one_line_profile: Generative model for synthesizable molecules
detailed_description: A tool implementing a generative model designed to search for and generate molecules that are chemically synthesizable, based on the paper 'A Model to Search for Synthesizable Molecules'.

name: mlearn
one_line_profile: Benchmark suite for machine learning interatomic potentials
detailed_description: A benchmark suite for evaluating machine learning interatomic potentials for materials, providing datasets and evaluation metrics for various material systems.

name: Polaris
one_line_profile: Hub for AI models, datasets, and benchmarks in drug discovery
detailed_description: A platform and library designed to foster the development of impactful AI models in drug discovery. It provides a hub for hosting datasets, benchmarks, and models, facilitating reproduction and comparison of ADMET and other drug discovery tasks.

name: DrugOOD
one_line_profile: OOD Dataset Curator and Benchmark for AI-aided Drug Discovery
detailed_description: A comprehensive benchmark and dataset curator for Out-Of-Distribution (OOD) generalization in AI-aided drug discovery. It provides tools to curate datasets with various domain shifts and evaluate model robustness.

name: MOOD
one_line_profile: Benchmark suite for molecular out-of-distribution generalization
detailed_description: MOOD (Molecular Out-Of-Distribution) is a benchmark framework designed to evaluate the robustness and generalization of machine learning models in drug discovery. It provides diverse data splitting protocols and metrics to simulate realistic discovery scenarios where test data differs distributionally from training data.

name: REINVENT (Legacy)
one_line_profile: Molecular de novo design using RNNs and Reinforcement Learning
detailed_description: The original implementation of REINVENT, a tool for de novo molecular design using recurrent neural networks and reinforcement learning to generate molecules with desired properties.

name: AiZynthFinder
one_line_profile: A tool for retrosynthetic planning using deep learning
detailed_description: AiZynthFinder is a tool for retrosynthetic planning that uses Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) combined with neural networks to predict reaction templates and solve synthesis routes.

name: ACPC
one_line_profile: Chemoinformatics tool for ligand-based virtual screening
detailed_description: ACPC (Auto-Correlation of Partial Charges) is a tool for ligand-based virtual screening that utilizes physicochemical property fields to compare molecules.

name: VirtualFlow for Ligand Preparation (VFLP)
one_line_profile: Workflow for large-scale ligand preparation
detailed_description: VFLP is a module of the VirtualFlow platform dedicated to the preparation of ligand libraries for virtual screening, handling tasks like format conversion and protonation.

name: VirtualFlow Utility (VFU)
one_line_profile: Streamlined version of VirtualFlow combining screening and preparation
detailed_description: VFU combines the functionalities of VirtualFlow for Virtual Screening (VFVS) and Ligand Preparation (VFLP) into a more streamlined utility for managing drug discovery workflows.

name: VirtualFlow for Virtual Screening (VFVS)
one_line_profile: Platform for ultra-large-scale virtual screening
detailed_description: VFVS is a workflow platform designed for ultra-large-scale virtual screening on computer clusters, supporting various docking programs and managing massive ligand libraries.

name: AIAgents4Pharma
one_line_profile: AI Agents framework for pharmaceutical R&D automation
detailed_description: A framework for building and deploying AI agents to automate various tasks in drug discovery and development, facilitating interaction with data and tools.

name: DrugEx (XuhanLiu)
one_line_profile: Deep learning toolkit for multi-objective drug design
detailed_description: A comprehensive toolkit for de novo drug design using deep learning, featuring Pareto-based multi-objective optimization to balance polypharmacology and other properties.

name: AutoGrow4
one_line_profile: Semi-automated computer-aided drug discovery using genetic algorithms
detailed_description: An open-source program for semi-automated computer-aided drug discovery that uses a genetic algorithm to evolve predicted ligands on demand, generating novel drug-like molecules and optimizing preexisting ligands.

name: OpenVS
one_line_profile: AI accelerated virtual screening platform for drug discovery
detailed_description: A platform combining artificial intelligence with traditional virtual screening methods to accelerate the drug discovery process, providing scripts and codes for high-throughput screening tasks.

name: AlzyFinder
one_line_profile: Web-based platform for ligand-based virtual screening and network pharmacology
detailed_description: A web-based platform designed for ligand-based virtual screening and network pharmacology analysis, facilitating the identification of potential drug candidates.

name: DataWarrior
one_line_profile: Interactive data analysis and visualization with chemical intelligence
detailed_description: An open-source program for interactive data analysis and visualization that understands chemical structures, widely used for exploring structure-activity relationships (SAR) in drug discovery.
